From: Cloud-build patches for jami-client-android
Subject: Add explicit -module JamiService to make-swig.sh

Jami's jni_interface.i declares
  %module (directors="1") JamiService
on line 19. SWIG 4.4.1 (current brew) and Jami's own build-from-source
SWIG 4.2.1 both fail to parse the parenthesized-attribute form when
invoked without an explicit -module flag — they emit a stderr warning
"No module name specified using %module or -module." then silently exit
with code 1 after "Generating wrappers...", before the script's
post-processing steps (jamiservice_loader.c generation, append to
jami_wrapper.cpp) can run.

The script has `set -e`, so the silent exit-1 from SWIG kills the
script with no further output — the symptom is a hung build with no
error message.

Adding `-module JamiService` makes SWIG happy regardless of the .i
file's %module directive form. The Java -package, output paths, and
all other behavior are unchanged.
---
 daemon/bin/jni/make-swig.sh | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/daemon/bin/jni/make-swig.sh b/daemon/bin/jni/make-swig.sh
index 0000000..0000000 100755
--- a/daemon/bin/jni/make-swig.sh
+++ b/daemon/bin/jni/make-swig.sh
@@ -41,7 +41,7 @@ PACKAGE_PATH="$PACKAGEDIR/${PACKAGE//.//}"
 mkdir -p $PACKAGE_PATH

 echo "Generating jami_wrapper.cpp and java bindings to $PACKAGE_PATH"
-swig -v -c++ -java \
+swig -v -c++ -java -module JamiService \
 -package $PACKAGE \
 -outdir $PACKAGE_PATH \
 -o $JNIDIR/jami_wrapper.cpp $JNIDIR/jni_interface.i
